               <msContents>
                  <summary>From Satornilus to Apollonios, referring to the difficulty of getting a boat in order to carry a body to Alexandria and to some delay in the preparation of the body.  He got one through the intervention of Clematius the chief priest, who sent a skiff of 60 artabs burthen.  He seeks from Apollonios a letter which those bearing the body  can carry with them to avoid trouble                                                                  of some kind during the journey</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; address on back</note>
                     <note type="general">29 lines; complete</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is a fluent cursive</note>
